    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6861" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὁπλίζω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅπλον</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὥπλισσε</span>,
          imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὥπλισσον</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὁπλίσαι</span>, mid. aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὁπλἵσ̓σατο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">equip, make ready</span>, as a
          chariot, a ship for sailing, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">prepare</span> a meal; mid.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">equip</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">arm oneself, prepare for
            oneself</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.526</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.453</span></i>; aor. pass., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅπλισθεν γυναῖκες</span>, ‘arrayed themselves’ for
          the dance, <i><span class="en">Od. 23.143</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
